<div class="comments-body">
<p>The collaborative nature of SpamNet is it's achilles heel. Legitimate newsletters are frequently flagged as spam because users are too lazy to unsubscribe, and genuine spam will slip through if you download it ahead of other SpamNet users.<br />
I switched to POPFile a few months back, it catches 95% of my spam with 0 false positives.<br />
http://sourceforge.net/projects/popfile/</p>
